{"source_key":"sha256-d0cd95f7d5f39f4b80f68f088e38f04c","record_index":49,"record_hash":"sha256:c0b5e78ed6395a359792ab8bccc7699bfb06c9099d35a8c958a9cf9ad88d8abb","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:08:40.837Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 58aa44\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 943\nOutput:\n    35\t\n    36\tThe implementation has two parts:\n    37\t\n    38\t- Next.js server app with Drizzle/PlanetScale MySQL, cookie auth, device auth APIs, token\n    39\t  storage, cloud project APIs, and streaming Git proxy routes.\n    40\t- Rust workspace with one crate, `but-cloud-cli`, producing top-level\n    41\t  `but-login`, `but-sync`, `but-cloud`, and `but-takeover` binaries.\n    42\t\n    43\tConfiguration:\n    44\t\n    45\t```env\n    46\tDATABASE_HOST=\"aws.connect.psdb.cloud/gitbutler_dev\"\n    47\tDATABASE_USERNAME=\"<planetscale username>\"\n    48\tDATABASE_PASSWORD=\"<planetscale password>\"\n    49\tSESSION_SECRET=\"<random 32+ bytes>\"\n    50\tPIERRE_ORG_NAME=\"your-org\"\n    51\tPIERRE_PRIVATE_KEY=\"<PKCS8 PEM>\"\n    52\tBOWTIE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=\"http://localhost:3000\"\n    53\t```\n    54\t\n    55\tThe private key signs short-lived ES256 JWTs for code.storage. End users and CLI\n    56\tclients only see the GitButler Cloud URL. Installed CLI binaries default to\n    57\t`https://gitbutler.dev`; local development uses `but-login --server\n    58\thttp://localhost:3000` or a stored CLI config override.\n    59\t\n    60\tCLI auth config stores multiple accounts keyed by `server_url + username`. A\n    61\tsuccessful login sets the global default server and user. Repository-local\n    62\t`.git/config` can override either value for testing:\n    63\t\n    64\t```bash\n    65\tgit config --local gitbutler.cloudServerUrl http://localhost:3000\n    66\tgit config --local gitbutler.cloudUser schacon2\n    67\t```\n    68\t\n    69\tServer-generated public URLs use `BOWTIE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL` when set and otherwise\n    70\tfall back to `https://gitbutler.dev`. Local `.env` files should keep\n    71\t`BOWTIE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=\"http://localhost:3000\"` so browser/device flows and\n    72\tclone URLs point at the development server.\n    73\t\n    74\t## Deployment Plan\n    75\t\n    76\tEvery environment uses PlanetScale MySQL. Development and production differ by\n    77\twhich PlanetScale database/branch credentials are placed in environment\n    78\tvariables.\n    79\t\n    80\tDatabase configuration:\n    81\t\n    82\t1. `DATABASE_HOST`, `DATABASE_USERNAME`, and `DATABASE_PASSWORD` are required.\n    83\t2. `DATABASE_HOST` may include the database path, for example\n    84\t   `aws.connect.psdb.cloud/gitbutler_dev`.\n    85\t3. If `DATABASE_HOST` does not include `/database`, set `DATABASE_NAME`.\n    86\t4. `DATABASE_QUERY` is optional and defaults to `sslaccept=strict`.\n    87\t5. The app and Drizzle scripts derive `DATABASE_URL` from those pieces at runtime.\n    88\t\n    89\tDevelopment environment:\n    90\t\n    91\t1. Create a PlanetScale development database or branch.\n    92\t2. Store its connection pieces in local `.env`.\n    93\t3. Keep `BOWTIE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=\"http://localhost:3000\"`.\n    94\t4. Run `pnpm drizzle:push` or `pnpm db:push` to update the development branch schema.\n    95\t5. Test CLI flows with `but-login --server http://localhost:3000`; the stored\n    96\t   CLI config makes later commands use the local server until login is changed.\n    97\t\n    98\tProduction environment:\n    99\t\n   100\t1. Deploy the Next.js app with `BOWTIE_PUBLIC_BASE_URL=\"https://gitbutler.dev\"`.\n   101\t2. Create a PlanetScale production branch password for the app.\n   102\t3. Store `DATABASE_HOST`, `DATABASE_USERNAME`, and `DATABASE_PASSWORD` only in\n   103\t   the deployment secret store.\n   104\t4. Apply schema changes to PlanetScale through its deploy-request workflow, not\n   105\t   ad hoc production `db push`.\n   106\t5. Keep `SESSION_SECRET`, `PIERRE_ORG_NAME`, `PIERRE_PRIVATE_KEY`, and database\n   107\t   credentials in deployment secrets.\n   108\t\n   109\tThe Drizzle schema lives in `db/schema.ts`; `drizzle-kit push` applies schema\n   110\tupdates to the PlanetScale branch selected by the current environment.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:08:40.837Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}